		<td><b>I discovered a glitch in Xenoblade Chronicles 2 (*spoilers*)</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I posted the details to my Google+ profile here (also includes a screenshot):<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://plus.google.com/u/0/+DennisJenkins75/posts/gtHb46oEXEt">https://plus.google.com/u/0/+DennisJenk ... tHb46oEXEt</a><!-- m --><br /><br />**spoilers**<br />**spoilers**<br />**spoilers**<br />**spoilers**<br />**spoilers**<br />**spoilers**<br />**spoilers**<br />**spoilers**<br /><br /><br /><br /><br />I do not know if all of these steps are required, but this is what I did:<br /><br />1) Game version: 1.5.0<br />2) Be in New Game +.<br />3) Right before reaching Genbu's Crown (in Tantal) and triggering the Ahkos cut-scene, send Pyra on a long Merc mission.<br />4) Note that Pyra is not in your party.<br />5) Continue into Genbu's Crown, trigger the cut-scene. Note that Pyra is present in the cut scene, but not in the fight with Ahkos and later Jin.<br />6) Pyra surrenders to Jin, and leaves the party.<br />7) Party returns to Tantal, Rex rage-quitting cut-scene, player control returns and next task is to visit King of Tantal.<br />8) Run around Tantal wasting time. Merc mission ends. Pyra reports success.<br />9) Send Pyra on another long Merc mission.<br />10) Visit the Tantal King, go to Leftheria, enter Spirit Crucible Elpys.<br />11) Cancel Pyra's Merc mission.<br />12) Go change Rex's active blade. You can now select Pyra, even though she's also held by Torna at the World Tree.<br />13) Proceed to get the 3rd Aegis blade w/ Pyra in team.<br /><br />I have not attempted a second repro of the above to see if some steps can be omitted. Getting this far in NG+ takes a few hours (less if you skip the cut-scenes) and I don't want to redo all of it. Hoping that someone else can confirm this glitch.

		

